[
    {
        "text": "Hi, I'm Francis, ",
        "start": 5.561,
        "duration": 1.482
    },
    {
        "text": "the host of this show \"Cooking with Dog.\"",
        "start": 7.043,
        "duration": 3.098
    },
    {
        "text": "First, rinse the moyashi bean sprouts ",
        "start": 25.548,
        "duration": 3.056
    },
    {
        "text": "and trim off the root ends.",
        "start": 28.604,
        "duration": 2.681
    },
    {
        "text": "Place them into a pan.",
        "start": 35.969,
        "duration": 2.719
    },
    {
        "text": "Add a sprinkle of salt ",
        "start": 40.138,
        "duration": 2.531
    },
    {
        "text": "and the sesame oil.",
        "start": 43.672,
        "duration": 2.493
    },
    {
        "text": "Cover ",
        "start": 47.075,
        "duration": 2.018
    },
    {
        "text": "and turn on the burner.",
        "start": 49.093,
        "duration": 2.877
    },
    {
        "text": "Heat the pan for 2 minutes.",
        "start": 51.97,
        "duration": 3.08
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, roughly stir the moyashi to help cook evenly.",
        "start": 61.021,
        "duration": 4.701
    },
    {
        "text": "Place onto a mesh strainer.",
        "start": 73.044,
        "duration": 3.234
    },
    {
        "text": "Cool the moyashi with a fan to avoid overcooking.",
        "start": 79.432,
        "duration": 4.583
    },
    {
        "text": "Next, let's make the sauce.",
        "start": 85.261,
        "duration": 2.717
    },
    {
        "text": "Combine the sugar, soy sauce, ",
        "start": 89.329,
        "duration": 3.799
    },
    {
        "text": "vinegar ",
        "start": 93.128,
        "duration": 2.671
    },
    {
        "text": "and the water.",
        "start": 95.799,
        "duration": 4.151
    },
    {
        "text": "Stir and dissolve the sugar.",
        "start": 99.95,
        "duration": 3.324
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, add the grated ginger root ",
        "start": 105.331,
        "duration": 3.301
    },
    {
        "text": "and the sesame oil.",
        "start": 109.819,
        "duration": 2.197
    },
    {
        "text": "Mix it again.",
        "start": 112.984,
        "duration": 2.202
    },
    {
        "text": "Save 2 tablespoonfuls of the sauce on a plate.",
        "start": 120.937,
        "duration": 4.051
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, let's prepare the shirataki noodles.",
        "start": 127.308,
        "duration": 4.13
    },
    {
        "text": "Rinse the shirataki and cut the long noodles ",
        "start": 131.438,
        "duration": 3.123
    },
    {
        "text": "into shorter lengths with kitchen shears.",
        "start": 134.561,
        "duration": 3.734
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, place the shirataki into a pot of boiling water.",
        "start": 139.03,
        "duration": 5.081
    },
    {
        "text": "Bring it to a rolling boil ",
        "start": 144.111,
        "duration": 2.394
    },
    {
        "text": "and boil the noodles for about 30 seconds.",
        "start": 146.505,
        "duration": 4.304
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, strain the shirataki ",
        "start": 151.758,
        "duration": 3.051
    },
    {
        "text": "and discard the water from the pot.",
        "start": 158.427,
        "duration": 3.003
    },
    {
        "text": "Place the shirataki back into the empty pot.",
        "start": 164.063,
        "duration": 3.718
    },
    {
        "text": "Turn the heat up to high ",
        "start": 168.265,
        "duration": 2.369
    },
    {
        "text": "and stir to remove any excess water.",
        "start": 170.634,
        "duration": 3.97
    },
    {
        "text": "This will help the noodles absorb the sauce later.",
        "start": 175.255,
        "duration": 4.051
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, place the shirataki onto the plate.",
        "start": 182.688,
        "duration": 3.688
    },
    {
        "text": "Toss to coat with the sauce evenly.",
        "start": 187.645,
        "duration": 3.022
    },
    {
        "text": "Chill the shirataki and the remaining sauce in the fridge.",
        "start": 191.567,
        "duration": 4.447
    },
    {
        "text": "And now, place the toppings onto the noodles.",
        "start": 197.648,
        "duration": 3.59
    },
    {
        "text": "Add the shredded cucumber ",
        "start": 202.507,
        "duration": 3.046
    },
    {
        "text": "and the tomato.",
        "start": 205.553,
        "duration": 2.539
    },
    {
        "text": "This Chinese-flavored barbecued pork is called ",
        "start": 208.092,
        "duration": 3.149
    },
    {
        "text": "Char Siu but you can substitute ham instead.",
        "start": 211.241,
        "duration": 4.624
    },
    {
        "text": "Add the Kinshi Tamago, shredded fried egg sheet ",
        "start": 217.623,
        "duration": 4.06
    },
    {
        "text": "and the moyashi bean sprouts.",
        "start": 224.713,
        "duration": 2.652
    },
    {
        "text": "Finally, lightly stir the sauce ",
        "start": 228.38,
        "duration": 2.485
    },
    {
        "text": "and pour it over the Hiyashi Chuka.",
        "start": 230.865,
        "duration": 3.405
    },
    {
        "text": "You can also add karashi hot mustard to taste.",
        "start": 234.27,
        "duration": 4.293
    },
    {
        "text": "Even if the package says parboiling is not required, ",
        "start": 238.563,
        "duration": 4.034
    },
    {
        "text": "we strongly recommend boiling the shirataki.",
        "start": 242.597,
        "duration": 3.357
    },
    {
        "text": "This will help it to absorb the sauce ",
        "start": 245.954,
        "duration": 2.313
    },
    {
        "text": "and reduce any unwanted flavor.",
        "start": 248.267,
        "duration": 3.067
    },
    {
        "text": "Shirataki has very low calories so it is perfect for dieting.",
        "start": 256.623,
        "duration": 5.417
    },
    {
        "text": "It is also rich in dietary fibers ",
        "start": 262.04,
        "duration": 3.051
    },
    {
        "text": "and helps maintain your digestive system.",
        "start": 265.091,
        "duration": 3.202
    },
    {
        "text": "Good luck in the kitchen!",
        "start": 268.293,
        "duration": 1.708
    }
]